Two Governors and 10 MPs who lost in the JP primaries in the North Rift region are now pondering on life outside power and active politics.Most of them have conceded defeat and said they will move on with life, but they are close allies of Deputy President William Ruto and will be hoping to get state jobs as promised by President Uhuru Kenyatta and the DP.Nandi Governor Cleophas Lagat, who lost to Senator Stephen Sang, said he accepts the people&rsquo;s verdict and will support the winner because he believes in democracy. &ldquo;Elective politics is that way. When the people decide, you respect their wish,&rdquo; he told the Star.Baringo Governor Benjamin Cheboi, who lost to Stanley Kiptis, complained of irregularities but was yet to announce his next move. However, his close aides said he would engage in private business.In Uasin Gishu, Senator Isaac Melly (pictured) lost to Prof Margaret Kamar in the primaries. Melly came third in the race and went quiet after the results were announced. He was unavailable to comment on his next move.